<H1>ISAAC</H1>
<H2>Internet Security, Applications, Authentication and
Cryptography</H2>
<P>We are a new research group in the <!WA0><a
href="http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/"> Computer Science Division</a>
at the <!WA1><a href="http://www.berkeley.edu/">University of California,
Berkeley</a>.</P>

Our members are
<UL>
<LI><!WA2><A href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~brewer/">Eric Brewer</a>, Assistant Professor
<LI><!WA3><A href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~gauthier/">Paul Gauthier</a>, Graduate Student
<LI><!WA4><A href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~iang/">Ian Goldberg</a>, Graduate Student
<LI><!WA5><A href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~daw/">David Wagner</a>, Graduate Student
</UL>

Ongoing research includes
<ul>
<li> <!WA6><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~daw/ssl3.0.ps">Analysis of the SSL 3.0 protocol</a>
<li> <!WA7><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~daw/janus/">
	Janus, a secure environment for helper applications</a>
<li> <!WA8><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~iang/isaac/ipse.html">Internet Protocol Scanning Engine</a>
<li> <!WA9><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~iang/isaac/hardware/">Architectural considerations for
	cryptanalytic hardware</a>, Dave and Ian's
        <!WA10><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/~randy/Courses/CS252.S96/CS252.Intro.html">CS 252</a>
        project.
<li> A cryptographic integrity-verifying tool
</ul>

